The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to drilling reports, which involves text classification, information retrieval, and pattern analysis. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it covers NLP and related topics. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category, as the paper deals with retrieving information from large amounts of text data. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category, as the paper uses machine learning techniques for classification. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category, as the paper proposes a methodology for automatic classification of sentences in drilling reports. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category, as the paper deals with applying AI techniques to a specific domain.
